A recent study revealed that a sleep deficit over just five nights can harm heart function and increase the risk of cardiovascular disease and death.
Chronic sleep deprivation can stress the heart, especially for early risers, who face a higher risk of heart conditions.
Athletes and college students often overlook the importance of adequate sleep, impacting their performance.
Sleep issues in children can be hard to detect, and even one night of lost sleep can impair memory.
Lack of sleep affects hormones regulating appetite and metabolism, potentially leading to weight gain and health issues.
Women are particularly vulnerable to the health risks of sleep deprivation, with studies showing a higher likelihood of hypertension.
